<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES - CYLINDER HEAD (Reconditioning) - OIL
        SHIELD
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="2">
        <title>OIL SHIELD</title>
        <para>Replace with new oil shield (
            <emph type="bold">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350360">3.60</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            ).
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <important>
                <para>EARLY PRODUCTION ENGINES (S/N 520428 AND BELOW). THE VALVE STEM OIL SHIELDS USED ON THE INTAKE AND
                    EXHAUST VALVES ARE DIFFERENT. THE INTAKE OIL SHIELD IS MUCH SMALLER THAN THE EXHAUST OIL SHIELD. DO
                    NOT INTERCHANGE OIL SHIELDS BETWEEN THE INTAKE AND EXHAUST VALVES.
                </para>
            </important>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <important>
                <para>LATER PRODUCTION ENGINES (S/N 520428 AND UP) ARE NOT BUILT WITH THE INTAKE (SMALL) OIL SHIELD.
                    SERVICE OF EARLY PRODUCTION ENGINES NO LONGER REQUIRES INSTALLATION OF THE INTAKE OIL SHIELD, IT MAY
                    BE DELETED.
                </para>
            </important>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="ef4350359" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="cg10654" filename="../figcg1/CG10654.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 3.59 Testing Valve Rotator</caption>
        </figure>
